Partner at Fifty Years, investing in deep tech founders at the earliest stages. More about me: https://dscottphoenix.com

Previously, I was cofounder and CEO of Vicarious, an AGI and robotics startup backed by ~$250M from Dustin Moskovitz, Mark Zuckerberg, Elon Musk, Jeff Bezos, Founders Fund, Khosla Ventures, DCVC, 8VC, and many others. Vicarious was acquired by Alphabet in 2022. After the acquisition, I spent a year as the Chief Product & Revenue Officer of Intrinsic, Alphabet’s “other bet” focused on robotics and AI.

Before Vicarious, I was an entrepreneur in residence at Founders Fund, started a company in the Y Combinator 2008 batch, and built an open source game. I also invest in hard tech startups like Sila Nano, Psi Quantum, Verge Genomics, and Science, and advise venture funds like Felicis Ventures, Base10, and 8VC.

I’ve spent my career at the intersection of enterprise technology, innovation strategy, and institutional finance—guiding complex organizations through pivotal decisions about where to invest, what to build, and how to stay competitive in a rapidly evolving digital landscape.

title: Atlanta Partnership Director at Homeward
about:
John Fountain is a visionary for many Real Estate experts in Atlanta, GA. Some see him as a leader, and for others he is a mentor and an inspiration. Selling Real Estate since 1999 and being MEGA Agent who consistently produced $6-10 Million a year in sales since 2004, he has a career story that's truly unique. 

John was raised in Vicksburg, MS and moved to Atlanta, GA in 1991. He received a bachelor’s degree in English with a Certificate to Teach on a Secondary Level from LaGrange College.  John began selling Real Estate in 1999 and quickly became a multi-million dollar producer with The Condo Store, Coldwell Banker, and Remax Greater Atlanta. He was honored the role of the Team Leader at the Keller Williams Cityside office for The Rawls Group in April of 2008. John led his team from the #39 ranked office in the city of Atlanta and the #12 office in Cobb County for sold market share to #9 in Atlanta and #1 in Cobb County in 2.5 years, according to the Atlanta Business Chronicle. The Keller Williams First Atlanta Office a.k.a. "Sandy Springs" is ranked the #1 most profitable office in all of Keller Williams out of 670+ offices in 2010 and 2013. Sandy Springs has also been ranked #1 in Sold Volume in all of Atlanta for seven straight years 2009-2015 according to the Atlanta Business Chronicle.  John attributes this extraordinary success to the foundation tools and resources of Keller Williams as well as his own ability to utilize those and teach his agents to follow the Keller Williams business models from The Millionaire Real Estate Agent book by Gary Keller.

After leading the #1 real estate office in GA, John Launched The Heyl Group (THG) Atlanta Expansion Team in October of 2017.  THG Atlanta produced 29 Million in sold volume in 2018 and 60 Million in Sold Volume in 2019 under John's Leadership.  After multiplying THG Atlanta and promoting leaders within the company, John set out to help Launch a Tim Heyl sister Company, Homeward (www.homeward.com).  He is now serving as the Atlanta Partnership Director for Homeward, which is a "buy before you sell solution" making the home buying process more accessible for people everywhere.

title: Founder & CEO at WordCrafter, turn SERP intelligence into content that ranks. Previously: Head of Marketing at Hugging Face, co-founder & COO at MonkeyLearn.
about:
TL;DR:
🤖 Founder at WordCrafter, an SEO tool to turn SERP intelligence into content that ranks.
👨‍🎤 Before: Head of Marketing at HuggingFace. COO & Co-founder at MonkeyLearn (acquired)
🦾 11+ years of experience working in AI.

👋 Hello! I'm Federico, CEO & Founder of WordCrafter, an AI copilot for SEO teams. Our AI identifies your target keyword's search intents, pinpoints key topics and writes engaging content optimized for search engines.

Previously, I was the Head of Marketing at Hugging Face, the fastest-growing community and most used platform for machine learning. As the first marketing hire at Hugging Face, I played a pivotal role in driving revenue growth and establishing foundational marketing strategies. I contributed to the design, launch, and expansion of Hugging Face's paid offerings, developing and executing marketing channels that effectively generated leads and drove adoption. These initiatives were instrumental in scaling annual recurring revenue from $0.5M to $20M. Additionally, my efforts supported Hugging Face in securing a $100M Series C funding round at a $2B valuation in 2022.

Before Hugging Face, I co-founded MonkeyLearn, a platform for analyzing text data with machine learning. Customers like Snapchat, GitHub, Salesforce, Atlassian and Stanford University used MonkeyLearn to analyze text data like customer feedback or support tickets to get insights and automate manual tasks. For more than seven years, I was COO and led the company's go-to-market strategy, including marketing, sales, operations and customer success. MonkeyLearn was acquired by Medallia.

In my spare time, I love helping tech companies refine their go-to-market strategies as an advisor. I enjoy guiding them through GTM challenges, using my experience from past successes and failures to help them find practical, effective solutions. I aim to help these companies sharpen their decision-making, unlock new opportunities and grow faster.

I specialize in B2B SaaS and have deep expertise in marketing, sales, and customer success. Additionally, I know how to code and have over 11 years of experience working in artificial intelligence.

If you are working on any of these things, please reach out; it would be great to chat with you!

name: Borja González
title: | Experto en análisis digital y redes sociales | CEO & Cofundador en Séntisis Intelligence e YN+ | Transformación y estrategia digital | Inteligencia de negocios| Especialista en go to market SaaS |
about:
¿Cómo un entrenador de baloncesto se convierte en el CEO de una empresa de Inteligencia Artificial que lidera el análisis de datos?

Desde muy joven, la cancha de baloncesto me enseñó la importancia de la estrategia, la anticipación y, sobre todo, el trabajo en equipo.

Y es que cuando estás en la cancha, cada pase, cada jugada tiene un impacto: por lo que no es aconsejable recurrir a la improvisación. La misma mentalidad de juego la aplico hoy en mi carrera, donde transformo datos complejos en decisiones claras y estratégicas para las marcas.

Lo que inició como una visión enfocada en el análisis de datos, evolucionó hasta convertirse en Séntisis Intelligence, la compañía que fundé para interpretar con precisión las conversaciones del entorno digital y convertirlas en inteligencia estratégica.

Desde 2012, hemos ayudado a más de 100 grandes marcas, como Banco Santander, Heineken, Vodafone y LaLiga, a tomar decisiones informadas a partir del análisis profundo de las redes sociales, encuestas y experiencia de clientes.

Pero más que la tecnología en sí misma, me inspira dar un sentido más estratégico y humano al análisis de datos. Al igual que en una jugada de baloncesto, donde la conexión con el equipo y la intuición marcan la diferencia, el análisis de datos debe ir más allá de lo técnico: es una herramienta clave para anticipar cambios, comprender a los clientes en toda su complejidad y tomar decisiones con rapidez y precisión.

Ese es mi reto diario en Séntisis Intelligence y ahora, también con YN+, una nueva iniciativa que fortalece nuestra visión de ofrecer consultoría avanzada en un entorno digital en constante evolución. A través de YN+, expandimos nuestra capacidad de análisis más allá de las RRSS, consolidando nuestra presencia en un ecosistema de datos que abarca todas las dimensiones del ámbito digital.

Sigo entrenando baloncesto y, en cada partido, confirmo que la perseverancia y la pasión marcan la diferencia tanto en la cancha como en la construcción de proyectos sólidos. Del mismo modo, en Séntisis Intelligence e YN+ avanzamos con determinación, fortaleciendo cada estrategia y transformando cada desafío en una oportunidad de crecimiento.

¿Te interesa descubrir cómo podemos transformar los datos de tu negocio en historias de éxito real y medible? Conectemos, será un placer para mí y para mi equipo acompañarte en este camino.

name: Jayasudan Munsamy
title: Social Entrepreneur at DeepVisionTech.AI - empowering Deaf, Speech & Hearing Impaired Community to 'live independently' with Let'sTalkSign interpretation platform
about:
Jayasudan Munsamy - Founder and CEO of DeepVisionTech.AI, a social startup with a vision to enabling 'independent living' for Persons with Disabilities (PwDs) through innovative AI-driven solutions. 

With over 25+ years of extensive global experience in Delivery Management, Business Development, Consulting, Product Management, Program Management, and Partner Management, Jayasudan has held leadership roles at Wipro, Infosys, Persistent, and Amazon before founding DeepVisionTech.AI in 2019.

In 2020, the organization pivoted on Let’sTalkSign - a suite of innovative solutions to empower the Deaf, Hard-of-Hearing, and Speech-Impaired community to 'live independently', by providing automatic Sign Language interpretation. Key variants of Let’sTalkSign include:

1. Communication & Assistant Apps: for Deaf individuals to communicate & get answers in Sign
2. Education Apps: for Deaf Students to learn in Sign, and for Teachers to teach in Sign.
3. Digital Accessibility tool: for Sign interpreting any digital content in websites and portals.
4. Workplace Inclusion Toolkit: Helps organizations provide reasonable accommodations for Deaf employees, boosting inclusivity and productivity.
5. Public Services Accessibility: Tailored solutions to make Government offices accessible to Deaf individuals.
6. Sign Language Chatbot: for providing engaging Customer Service to Deaf customers, in Sign.

To date, Let’sTalkSign has positively impacted lives of thousands of Deaf individuals, fostering independence and accessibility.

Specialising in AI/ML/GenAI-based solutions, Cloud, IoT and Mobile technologies, Jayasudan combines Technical expertise with a passion for Social Innovation. His leadership is driven by a mission to create meaningful, technology-enabled change for underserved communities.

Join us 🤝 in creating a more accessible & inclusive world 🌍 !

Explore more at https://DeepVisionTech.AI and https://LetsTalkSign.org.

Andre Esteva, PhD, is an American entrepreneur and AI scientist. ArteraAI was named a TIME 2024 Best Invention and selected for the World Economic Forum's Global Innovators as one of the world's top growth-stage companies.

His work is featured in Cell, The Lancet, NeurIPS, TIME, and widely covered by the WSJ, Fortune, BBC, The Economist, and hundreds of outlets.

He earned his PhD in Computer Vision at Stanford, and graduated with highest honors in Electrical Engineering and Pure Math from UT-Austin, where he was Engineering Valedictorian.

Lunar Outposts builds autonomous systems and infrastructure for space and extreme environments. name: John Ennis
title: President Aigora, CEO Tulle
about:
Life is full of surprises. I initially expected to become a math professor, but as I finished my PhD, I realized my passion lay in something more closely tied to real-world experience. This led me to a postdoc in computational neuroscience, programming neural networks to study human category learning.

After my postdoc, I spent ten enriching years as a market research consultant at The Institute for Perception. There, I discovered my love for the intersection of mathematics and sensory science, engaging in publishing, teaching, managing projects, and building meaningful connections. Eventually, I founded my own company, Aigora, dedicated to empowering sensory and consumer scientists to leverage artificial intelligence.

Driven by my conviction in AI’s transformative power, I also founded Tulle in 2022—an AI venture aimed at optimizing trade and exploring new frontiers in asset exchange. This period profoundly expanded my expertise in advanced AI implementation, startup scaling, fundraising, and overcoming the practical challenges of introducing groundbreaking technology to the market.

Recently, another unexpected turn arose when Aigora's president stepped down for personal reasons. Recognizing the need for experienced leadership—and seeing the AI-powered future I envisioned back in 2019 now becoming reality—I stepped back in as Chairman. While still guiding Tulle, my current focus is steering Aigora through its next crucial phase, ensuring we seize this transformative moment.

AI has matured significantly, finally acheiving it's full ability to deliver practical tools poised to reshape sensory and consumer science. Our goal at Aigora is integrating sophisticated AI systems deeply into our offerings and internal operations, drawing insights from foundational experiences at Aigora and cutting-edge advancements at Tulle.

We're shifting from isolated tools to embedding AI as intelligent "Thinking Partners" within workflows, aiming to augment teams, clarify goals, simplify complexity, accelerate insights, and unlock collective potential—potentially boosting productivity by 5x or more. We're pioneering this future within Aigora, embodying the transformation for which we advocate.

name: Colin Rule
title: CEO at odr.com
about:
Colin Rule is President and CEO of ODR.com/Mediate.com, acquired by the American Arbitration Association/International Centre for Dispute Resolution in May 2024. From 2003 to 2011 Colin was Director of ODR for eBay and PayPal. In 2011 Colin co-founded Modria.com, an ODR provider based in Silicon Valley, which was acquired by Tyler Technologies in 2017.  From 2017 to 2020 Colin served as Vice President of ODR at Tyler.

Colin has worked in the dispute resolution field for 30 years as a mediator, trainer, and consultant. He is currently Co-Chair of the Advisory Board at the National Center for Technology and Dispute Resolution at UMass-Amherst, a Non-Resident Fellow at the Gould Center for Conflict Resolution at Stanford Law School, and Practitioner-in-Residence at Texas A&M School of Law.

Colin co-founded Online Resolution, one of the first online dispute resolution (ODR) providers, in 1999 and served as its CEO and President. In 2002 Colin co-founded the Online Public Disputes Project, which applied ODR to multiparty, public disputes. Colin also worked for several years with the National Institute for Dispute Resolution in Washington, D.C. and the Consensus Building Institute in Cambridge, MA. 

Colin is the author of Online Dispute Resolution for Business (published by Jossey-Bass in September 2002) and co-author of The New Handshake: Online Dispute Resolution and the Future of Consumer Protection (published by the American Bar Association in 2017). He received the D'Alemberte-Raven Award from the American Bar Association in 2023, the first Frank Sander Award for Innovation in ADR from the ABA in 2020, and the Mary Parker Follett Award from the Association for Conflict Resolution in 2013.  He holds a Master's degree from Harvard University's Kennedy School of Government in conflict resolution and technology, a graduate certificate in dispute resolution from UMass-Boston, and a B.A. in Peace Studies from Haverford College.  He served as a Peace Corps volunteer in Eritrea from 1995-1997.

title: Co-Founder and CEO at Menten AI - We’re hiring!
about:
Menten AI is a drug discovery company focused on designing peptides for conditions with high unmet medical need. We develop computational methods for protein design that leverage machine learning and quantum computing.

I am interested in diverse applications of quantum computing and machine learning in health and social good. My expertise is in quantum optimization, reinforcement learning, and computer vision (Deep Learning - CNNs).  My research interests at the moment are quantum machine learning, constrained programming, meta-learning, few-shot learning, GAN's in general, and biologically inspired models. I have a technical background in Computational Neuroscience, Machine Learning, and Physics.

Aside from my research and entrepreneurial work, I also served as a Scientific Advisor for The Decision Lab.

name: Viswa Colluru, PhD
title: CEO & Founder at Enveda | We're hiring!
about:
I believe in the revolutionary power of technology, the monumental potential of human ingenuity, and radical empiricism as our primary tool to engineer around the complexity of natural systems. I’m working with a dream-team of co-believers to distill these elements into practice at Enveda Biosciences, where we’re building a platform to map the molecular patterns underlying humanity’s use of medicinal plants to systematically discover high-value transformative therapeutics. 

Prior to Enveda, I was a key early team member at Recursion, where I led the company's foray outside rare disease as an innovation scientist, articulated value propositions and delivered pitches around those platforms to multiple top 10 pharma partners as a discovery product manager, and switched hats a second time to set the commercial vision for internal drug candidates across multiple therapeutic areas (see https://medium.com/recursion-pharmaceuticals/celebrating-the-departure-of-an-outstanding-employee-65db2455fd1f). While in graduate school, I pioneered three technologies to improve cancer therapies by leveraging the patient's own immune system. 

I am passionate about creating meaningful, lasting impact geared towards maximizing the well-being of as many people on this planet as possible.

name: Weili Dai
title: Co-Founder & President, FLC Technology Group
about:
Weili Dai is one of the most successful women entrepreneurs in the world. Widely considered a technology visionary, she is the only woman Co-Founder of a global semiconductor company, Marvell Technology Group. For her contributions to technology and society, Newsweek named Ms. Dai one of the “150 Women Who Shake the World” and was profiled by CNN International for the Leading Women Series: Leading the Female Tech Charge, Leading Women Principles Fair and Care, Educating for Future Success, and Leading Women Inspire Others.

Forbes Magazine listed Ms. Dai as one of the “World’s 100 Most Powerful Women” and “America’s Richest Self-Made Women”. The Global Semiconductor Alliance (GSA) also recognized Ms. Dai along with her husband Dr. Sehat Sutardja, Co-Founder and former CEO of Marvell, with the prestigious 2013 Dr. Morris Chang Exemplary Leadership Award, due to their exceptional success in creating Marvell, their individual contributions to today’s modern semiconductor age, as well as the talents and expertise they’ve continuously leveraged to address and overcome pressing global issues like education and smart energy. 

Weili Dai holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science from the University of California at Berkeley. Today, “Sutardja Dai Hall” named after Ms. Dai along with her husband, Sehat Sutardja, is home to the Center for Information Technology Research in the Interest of Society (CITRIS). Celebrated as the glue behind her companies, family and community, Ms. Dai is the proud mother of two sons, Christopher and Nicholas, who both received their Ph.D degrees in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at UC Berkeley. Ms. Dai was selected as the first woman commencement speaker for the University of California, Berkeley, College of Engineering graduation ceremony on May 12, 2012.

Ms. Dai is the Chairwoman of Lark Health through which she has become a powerful advocate for the better use of technology to improve the human condition. She’s now an extremely proud grandmother and continues to have a relentless passion to innovate through her various active roles in semiconductor technology and software companies –including Silicon Box, as Co-Founder, FLC Technology Group as the Co-Founder and President, and MeetKai, as Co-Founder and Executive Chairwoman, where she’s shaping the future of AI experiences.

name: Nicholas Harris
title: CEO at Lightmatter
about:
---Bio---
With over 50 patents and 80 publications in journals including Nature, Nicholas’ seminal work on quantum and classical information processing with integrated photonics has helped launch the international research field of programmable photonics. In 2021, MIT Technology Review honored Nicholas with the Innovators Under 35 award, selected by 30 judges—including Andrew Ng—from over 500 nominees. Past winners include Google’s Larry Page and Sergey Brin, Facebook’s Mark Zuckerberg, and Apple’s Jony Ive. He received his doctorate in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology where he was a National Science Foundation Graduate Research Fellow and then a Postdoctoral Fellow through the Intelligence Community Postdoctoral Fellowship.

---Perspective---
My career has been focused on understanding computers—how they work (down to the atomic scale) and where they are headed. During my time at MIT as a PhD student and post-doctoral fellow, I explored what may become the ultimate tool for understanding the exquisite details of our universe: quantum computers. Quantum computing is profoundly exciting, but supporting hardware technologies are not ready yet. I've developed a level of expertise in designing components and systems that create, process, and detect light and what I've been able to build leads me to believe that the next step in the evolution of computing is all about light. I founded Lightmatter with a mission of creating photonic computers and new ways for chips to communicate. We are building machines that will serve as a new engine for human progress.

I have built my career at the intersection of language, leadership, and technology, managing high-stakes communication and leading diverse teams across four continents. I believe that, much like interpreting, leadership requires deep listening, the ability to anticipate challenges, and the agility to make split-second decisions with clarity and confidence.

Through mentoring, coaching, and storytelling, I help leaders and organizations refine their message, inspire action, and connect with their audiences in meaningful ways. My experience working across industries has shown me that the principles of high-stakes interpretation—focus, adaptability, and precision—are just as critical in boardrooms as they are in live events.

As communication continues to evolve, I remain focused on helping businesses and professionals navigate the changes ahead. Whether it’s high-stakes messaging, cross-cultural strategy, or the future of AI and human expertise, my work is centered on one goal: helping people communicate more effectively, think more clearly, and lead with confidence in an unpredictable world.
